RFID TOURIST UUID SYSTEM — FULL WORKFLOW

---

1. OVERVIEW

---

Goal:
Store a unique UUID for each tourist on an RFID card.
Use ESP32 / ESP8266 + RC522 to write/read data.
Sync everything with a backend server and website.

Core Idea:

* RFID card stores ONLY UUID
* Backend stores full tourist data
* ESP acts as bridge between RFID and backend

---

2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

---

[ Website (Admin Panel) ]
↓
[ Backend API (Node.js / Flask) ]
↓
[ ESP32 / ESP8266 (WiFi) ]
↓
[ RC522 RFID Module ]
↓
[ RFID Card (UUID stored) ]

---

3. DATA FLOW

---

A. REGISTER TOURIST
admin slsect theusers 
auto add the the tourist id 

B. WRITE TO RFID

1. Admin clicks "Write कार्ड"
2. Backend marks UUID as "pending write"
3. ESP fetches UUID via API
4. Tourist taps RFID card
5. ESP writes UUID to card
6. ESP sends success response to backend

C. READ FROM RFID

1. Tourist taps card
2. ESP reads UUID
3. ESP sends UUID to backend
4. Backend returns tourist data
5. Data displayed on website/dashboard

---

4. HARDWARE SETUP

---

Components:

* ESP32 or ESP8266 (CH340 USB supported)
* RC522 RFID Module
* RFID Cards

ESP32 Wiring:
SDA (SS) → GPIO 5
SCK      → GPIO 18
MOSI     → GPIO 23
MISO     → GPIO 19
RST      → GPIO 22
3.3V     → 3.3V
GND      → GND

ESP8266 Wiring:
SDA → D2
SCK → D5
MOSI → D7
MISO → D6
RST → D1

---

5. BACKEND API DESIGN

---



POST /write-success
→ ESP confirms write complete

POST /scan
→ Input: UUID
→ Returns tourist data

